{% extends 'emails/onboarding/onboarding_email_base.html.twig' %}

{% block preheader %}
    Under HIPAA, the FTC Safeguards Rule, or ABA Ethics, compliance is your shield.
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <row class="content-body">
        <columns>
            <h2>Zero-Knowledge E2EE: Your Cryptographic Shield</h2>

            <p>Dear {{ recipient_name }},</p>

            <p>Whether your firm is subject to the <strong>HIPAA Security Rule</strong> (healthcare), the <strong>FTC Safeguards Rule & IRS Pub 4557</strong> (tax/accounting), or <strong>ABA Model Rule 1.6(c)</strong> (legal), you have a federal and ethical obligation to safeguard customer data in transit and at rest.</p>

            <p>Standard cloud storage providers encrypt your files, but <em>they hold the decryption keys</em>. If their databases are breached, your clients' private documents are exposed, and your firm is liable.</p>

            <p>FileDrop Pro uses a local double-envelope cryptographic system executing entirely inside the browser:</p>

            <!-- Interactive Cryptographic Steps -->
            <div class="step-block">
                <h3>How your secure envelope works:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>When a client drops a file, their browser generates a unique, symmetric AES-256 session key (<strong>K<sub>sym</sub></strong>) to encrypt the document locally in memory.</li>
                    <li>That key is immediately wrapped ("encrypted") using your firm's asymmetric Public Key (<strong>K<sub>pub</sub></strong>):
                        <div class="math-block">
                            WrappedKey = RSA-OAEP( K<sub>sym</sub> using K<sub>pub</sub> )
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li>The encrypted file is sent directly to AWS S3, and the wrapped key is stored in our database.</li>
                    <li><strong>Our servers never touch the raw session key.</strong> When you open the file, your browser decrypts the wrapped key locally using your private master password, keeping your data entirely secure from external threats.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="compliance-callout">
                🛡️ <strong>Need a signed BAA?</strong> We sign Business Associate Agreements (BAA) for our healthcare clients on standard Pro and Enterprise subscription tiers.
            </div>

            <spacer size="16"></spacer>

            <!-- Upgrade CTA -->
            <button href="{{ billing_url }}" class="btn-cta">
                Secure Your Compliance Shield (Upgrade Plan)
            </button>
        </columns>
    </row>
{% endblock %}
